{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Poly Extrude"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 17], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [157, 200], "text": ["Extrudes polygonal faces and edges."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [262, 362], "text": ["Poly Extrude lets you \"pull\" faces and edges out to create new columns/sheets of polygons."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [362, 442], "text": ["You can make the extrusion bigger or smaller (inset/outset), and twist it."]}], "indent": 0, "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_simple.jpg", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_simple.jpg"}], "role": "item", "extent": [215, 262], "type": "fig"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [496, 571], "text": ["If you extrude interior edges, the node will use the surface normals."]}], "indent": 0, "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_edges_interior.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_edges_interior.png"}], "role": "item", "extent": [442, 496], "type": "fig"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [625, 702], "text": ["If you extrude boundary edges, the node will use the surface direction."]}], "indent": 0, "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_edges_boundary.jpg", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_edges_boundary.jpg"}], "role": "item", "extent": [571, 625], "type": "fig"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [747, 874], "text": ["You can set the number of divisions in the extrusion and have the extrusion curve from the source to the destination."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [874, 954], "text": ["You can draw a curve and have the extrusion follow the shape of the curve."]}], "indent": 0, "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_curve.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_curve.png"}], "role": "item", "extent": [702, 747], "type": "fig"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "fig_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [954, 1255], "text": ["The node creates a copy of the selected components and transforms them according the parameters, then builds a polygonal bridge between them. The original components are called the ", {"text": ["back"], "type": "em"}, " of the extrusion (drawn in red), and the copied/transformed components are called the ", {"text": ["front"], "type": "em"}, " (drawn in green)."]}, {"body": [{"body": [], "indent": 0, "text": [" Polyextrude"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "142466795 "}, "extent": [1255, 1275], "type": "vimeo"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "vimeo_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [200, 215], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1347, 1401], "text": ["Select the edges or faces you want to extrude."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1401, 1484], "text": ["On the ", {"text": ["Model"], "type": "ui"}, " shelf, click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/SOP/polyextrude", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/polyextrude"}, " Poly Extrude tool."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1484, 1663], "text": ["Use the line handle to pull or push the extrusion front. Use the controls in the operation toolbar across the top of the viewport to set the inset and number of divisions."]}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": [" Extrude edges/faces"], "role": "item", "extent": [1317, 1347], "type": "task"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "task_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["How to"], "extent": [1296, 1317], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "howto"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [], "indent": 0, "text": [" Polyextrude curve input"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "142470680 "}, "extent": [1684, 1717], "type": "vimeo"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "vimeo_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1790, 1846], "text": ["Draw the curve you want the extrusion to follow."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1846, 1894], "text": ["Extrude the edges/faces (see above)."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1894, 1964], "text": ["Connect the curve to the Poly Extrude node\u2019s second input."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [1964, 2053], "text": ["In the Poly Extrude parameters, set ", {"text": ["Spine shape"], "type": "ui"}, " to \"Curve from second input\"."]}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": [" Make the extrusion follow an external curve"], "role": "item", "extent": [1738, 1790], "type": "task"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "task_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Follow a curve"], "extent": [1663, 1684], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2135, 2240], "text": ["By default, the tool only extrudes along the normals, with controls for distance, inset, and twist."]}], "indent": 0, "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_simple.jpg", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_simple.jpg"}], "role": "item", "extent": [2088, 2135], "type": "fig"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2291, 2429], "text": ["You can optionally turn on the ", {"text": ["Transform extruded front"], "type": "ui"}, " to also apply a full move/rotate/scale transform to the extrusion front."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2429, 2592], "text": ["This transform is applied ", {"text": ["in addition to"], "type": "em"}, " the ", {"text": ["Distance"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Twist"], "type": "ui"}, " controls, so you probably want to set them to ", {"text": ["0"], "type": "code"}, " if you want to use the transform."]}], "indent": 0, "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_transformed.jpg", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_transformed.jpg"}], "role": "item", "extent": [2240, 2291], "type": "fig"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "fig_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Distance/twist vs. transform"], "extent": [2053, 2088], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2672, 2739], "text": ["The node automatically treats adjacent edges/faces as groups."]}], "indent": 0, "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_multi.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_multi.png"}], "role": "item", "extent": [2626, 2672], "type": "fig"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2789, 2870], "text": ["You can extrude individual edges/faces instead of treating them as a group."]}], "indent": 0, "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_individual.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_individual.png"}], "role": "item", "extent": [2739, 2789], "type": "fig"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "fig_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [2870, 2980], "text": ["The node transforms each element in its own space (unless you set ", {"text": ["Extrusion mode"], "type": "ui"}, " to \"Translate Global\")."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3068, 3314], "text": ["If you want to define multiple source loops with edges/faces that happen to be adjacent, they will just look like one thing to the node. You can choose a point/edge ", {"text": ["Split group"], "type": "ui"}, " that divides adjacent faces/edges into separate groups."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3314, 3414], "text": ["In this image, the yellow line is an edge group splitting the selected faces into two sources."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3414, 3537], "text": ["(If you are extruding edges, you split with a point group. If you are extruding faces, you split with an edge group.)"]}], "indent": 0, "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/bridge_split_group.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/bridge_split_group.png"}], "role": "item", "extent": [3017, 3068], "type": "fig"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "fig_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Splitting groups"], "extent": [2980, 3017], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "splitting"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Multiple extrusions"], "extent": [2592, 2626], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "multi"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3699, 3842], "text": ["If you want to vary some parameter per-primitive/edge, store the value in an attribute and use the controls on the ", {"text": ["Local Control"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Unlike previous versions of PolyExtrude, this node ", {"text": ["does not support local variables or per-primitive/edge expressions"], "type": "strong"}, ", for performance reasons."], "extent": [3549, 3699], "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet"}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Notes"], "extent": [3537, 3549], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3862, 3949], "text": ["Faces or edges to extrude. This can be the name of a primitive or edge group."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Group"], "role": "item", "extent": [3854, 3862], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5795, 5877], "text": ["Whether to treat adjacent edges/faces as a group, or as individuals."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4028, 4086], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_individual.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_individual.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Divide Into"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "splittype"}, "extent": [3949, 3962], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4124, 4384], "text": ["When ", {"text": ["Divide into"], "type": "ui"}, " is \"Connected components\", any adjacent elements are treated as a single group. If there are edges/faces that are adjacent but you want to be separate groups, you can split them using this group. See ", {"fragment": "#splitting", "text": ["splitting"], "value": "#splitting", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/polyextrude#splitting", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, " above."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4384, 4434], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/bridge_split_group.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/bridge_split_group.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Split Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "splitgroup"}, "extent": [4086, 4099], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4450, 4500], "text": ["Which normals to use to extrude faces/edges."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [4527, 4661], "text": ["Extrude faces along their normals, extrude edges intelligently depending on whether they are interior or boundary edges."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [4500, 4527], "text": ["Primitive/Edge Normal"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [4679, 4717], "text": ["Extrude along point normals."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [4661, 4679], "text": ["Point Normal"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Extrusion Mode"], "role": "item", "extent": [4434, 4450], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4727, 4884], "text": ["How far (in Houdini units) to \"pull out\" the extrusion. You can use a negative number to \"push\" the extrusion in the opposite direction of the normals."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Distance"], "role": "item", "extent": [4717, 4727], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4907, 4997], "text": ["Expands or dilates the extrusion front. This has no effect when extruding edges."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [4997, 5042], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_inset.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_inset.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Inset"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "inset"}, "extent": [4884, 4891], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5069, 5133], "text": ["Twists the extrusion front around the extrusion spine."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5133, 5178], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_twist.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_twist.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Twist"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "twist"}, "extent": [5042, 5049], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5209, 5267], "text": ["The number of rows of polygons in the extrusion."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Divisions"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "divisions"}, "extent": [5178, 5189], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5304, 5370], "text": ["The path the extrusion takes between the back and front."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5384, 5434], "text": ["Straight from the back to the front."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [5370, 5384], "text": ["Straight"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5446, 5506], "text": ["Curve between the back and front orientations."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [5434, 5446], "text": ["Curved"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5535, 5609], "text": ["Take the shape of a curve connected to this node\u2019s second input."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [5506, 5535], "text": ["Curve From Second Input"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Spine shape"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "spinetype"}, "extent": [5267, 5280], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5702, 5962], "text": ["Turn this on to show full transformation (move, rotate, scale) controls for the extrusion front. This transform is applied ", {"text": ["in addition to"], "type": "em"}, " the ", {"text": ["Distance"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Twist"], "type": "ui"}, " controls, so you probably want to set them to ", {"text": ["0"], "type": "code"}, " if you want to use the transform."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Transform Extruded Front"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "xformfront"}, "extent": [5650, 5677], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [5998, 6091], "text": ["Order in which to apply local transformation (when ", {"text": ["Transform Extruded Front"], "type": "ui"}, " is on)."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Transformation Order"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "rst"}, "extent": [5962, 5984], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6122, 6210], "text": ["Order in which to apply local rotations (when ", {"text": ["Transform Extruded Front"], "type": "ui"}, " is on)."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Rotation Order"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "lxyz"}, "extent": [6091, 6107], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6245, 6424], "text": ["Moves the extrusion front (when ", {"text": ["Transform Extruded Front"], "type": "ui"}, " is on). The Z component controls the extrusion amount. The X and Y are applied to the front after extrusion."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6424, 6472], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_move.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_move.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Translate"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "translate"}, "extent": [6210, 6221], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6497, 6673], "text": ["Rotates the extrusion front (when ", {"text": ["Transform Extruded Front"], "type": "ui"}, " is on). You can use this to twist the extrusion, but see also ", {"text": ["Twist"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter for more information."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6673, 6723], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_rotate.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_rotate.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Rotate"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "rotate"}, "extent": [6472, 6480], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6750, 6829], "text": ["Scales the extrusion front (when ", {"text": ["Transform Extruded Front"], "type": "ui"}, " is on)."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6829, 6878], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_scale.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_scale.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Scale"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "scale"}, "extent": [6723, 6730], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [6905, 7081], "text": ["Shears the extrusion front (when ", {"text": ["Transform Extruded Front"], "type": "ui"}, " is on). The numbers represent X shear in XY plane, X shear in the XZ plane, and Y shear in the YZ plane."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [7081, 7130], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_shear.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_shear.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Shear"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "shear"}, "extent": [6878, 6885], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 5, "type": "para", "extent": [7154, 7354], "text": ["Local pivot point for moving, rotating, and scaling the extrusion front (when ", {"text": ["Transform Extruded Front"], "type": "ui"}, " is on). This is local to each front, unless ", {"text": ["Extrusion mode"], "type": "ui"}, " is  \"Global translate\"."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Pivot"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "pivot"}, "extent": [7130, 7137], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Front transform"], "extent": [5625, 5650], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [7430, 7561], "text": ["Generate polygons for the extrusion front. Turn this off if you only want the sides. This has no effect when extruding edges."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Output Front"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "outputfront"}, "extent": [7389, 7404], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [7599, 7762], "text": ["Enter the name to put the polygons of the extrusion front in this group. You can use this group name in later nodes to easily target just the front polygons."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Front Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "frontgroup"}, "extent": [7561, 7574], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [7800, 7902], "text": ["Turn this off to delete the original extruded polygons. This has no effect when extruding edges."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Output Back"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "outputback"}, "extent": [7762, 7775], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [7938, 8107], "text": ["Enter the name to put the polygons at the start of the extrusion in this group. You can use this group name in later nodes to easily target just the back polygons."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Back Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "backgroup"}, "extent": [7902, 7914], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [8146, 8302], "text": ["Generate polygons for the sides of the extrusion. If you turn this off, the node essentially is just a copy and translate of the selected edges/faces."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Output Side"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "outputsides"}, "extent": [8107, 8120], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [8338, 8500], "text": ["Enter the name to put the polygons in the extrusion sides in this group. You can use this group name in later nodes to easily target just the side polygons."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Side Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "sidegroup"}, "extent": [8302, 8314], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [8545, 8854], "text": ["Enter the name to put the edges bordering the front and side of the extrusion in this group. This group is equal to the front group when extruding edges. This group is empty when both ", {"text": ["Output Front"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Output Side"], "type": "ui"}, " are off. This group is highlighted green in the polyextrude state in the viewport."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Front Boundary Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "frontseamgrp"}, "extent": [8500, 8522], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [8897, 9126], "text": ["Enter the name to put the edges bordering the back and side of the extrusion in this group. This group is equal to the back group when extruding edges. This group is highlighted red in the polyextrude state in the viewport."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Back Boundary Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "backseamgrp"}, "extent": [8854, 8875], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [9172, 9302], "text": ["If the original edges/faces were in any groups, add the corresponding edges/faces in the extrusion front to the same groups."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Preserve Groups"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "preservegroups"}, "extent": [9126, 9143], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Output Geometry and Groups"], "extent": [7354, 7389], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [9363, 9748], "text": ["When this is on, the extrusion front cannot be inset beyond a point where the node determines it would create a degenerate, pinched, zero-size, or otherwise undesirable front. If you turn this off, insetting can continue to shrink the front through pinching and then invert so that further insetting actually grows the front. You should generally just leave this on all the time."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Limit insetting"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "limitinset"}, "extent": [9320, 9338], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [9792, 10086], "text": ["If you are extruding multiple fronts, as you increase ", {"text": ["Inset"], "type": "ui"}, ", once one front has a zero-size edge, all fronts stop shrinking. Turn this off to allow each front to shrink to zero individually as you increase ", {"text": ["Inset"], "type": "ui"}, ". If ", {"text": ["Limit insetting to zero size"], "type": "ui"}, " is off, this option is ignored."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Use common limit"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "commonlimit"}, "extent": [9748, 9766], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Insetting"], "extent": [9302, 9320], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [10102, 10218], "text": ["By default, if the input geometry has normal attributes, the node adds those attributes to the extruded geometry."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [10269, 10384], "text": ["Add vertex normals. If vertex normals existed on the original selected edges/faces, the node overwrites them."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Add Vertex Normals"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "addvertexnormals"}, "extent": [10218, 10238], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [10420, 10535], "text": ["Vertices across a shared edge will have different normals if the face normals differ by more than this angle."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cusp Angle"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "csupangle"}, "extent": [10384, 10396], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [10590, 10679], "text": ["Always cusp boundary edges of the extrusion front, ignoring the ", {"text": ["Cusp angle"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cusp All Front Boundary Edges"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "cuspfront"}, "extent": [10535, 10566], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [10732, 10820], "text": ["Always cusp boundary edges of the extrusion back, ignoring the ", {"text": ["Cusp angle"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cusp All Back Boundary Edges"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "cuspback"}, "extent": [10679, 10709], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Normals"], "extent": [10086, 10102], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Extrusion"], "extent": [5609, 5625], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [10840, 10937], "text": ["Bridging tab controls several details of how the bridge connecting the back and front behaves."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [11009, 11159], "text": ["How much the orientation of the front affects the direction of the extrusion at that end. Only available when ", {"text": ["Spine shape"], "type": "ui"}, " is not \"Straight\"."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [11159, 11258], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_magnitude1.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_magnitude1.png"}, "\n    ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_magnitude2.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_magnitude2.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Front Magnitude"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "frontmagnitude"}, "extent": [10962, 10980], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [11302, 11467], "text": ["How much the orientation of the original edges/faces affects the direction of the extrusion at that end. Only available when ", {"text": ["Spine shape"], "type": "ui"}, " is not \"Straight\"."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Back Magnitude"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "backmagnitude"}, "extent": [11258, 11274], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [11513, 11652], "text": ["How far the extrusion path follows the orientation of the extrusion front. Only available when ", {"text": ["Spine shape"], "type": "ui"}, " is not \"Straight\"."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [11652, 11751], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_stiffness1.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_stiffness1.png"}, "\n    ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/model/extrude_stiffness2.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/model/extrude_stiffness2.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Front Stiffness"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "frontstiffness"}, "extent": [11467, 11484], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [11791, 11938], "text": ["How far the path of the extrusion follows the orientation of the original edges/faces. Only available when ", {"text": ["Spine shape"], "type": "ui"}, " is not \"Straight\"."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Back Stiffness"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "backstiffness"}, "extent": [11751, 11767], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [11975, 12239], "text": ["A technical parameter of the node\u2019s internal algorithm. \"Rotating frame\" tends to be better for twisting bridges, but in practice there\u2019s no good basis for choosing one or the other. You can try both and see if they make a difference for your bridge.        "]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Interpolation"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "morphmethod"}, "extent": [11938, 11953], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [9420, 9485], "text": ["Controls the spacing of the divisions along the bridge."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "extent": [9498, 9527], "text": ["Spaced equally."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "extent": [9485, 9498], "text": ["Uniform"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "extent": [9552, 9642], "text": ["Uses more polygons in high curvature areas and fewer polygons in straight areas."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "extent": [9527, 9552], "text": ["Curvature Sensitive"]}], "type": "dt_group", "container": true}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Spacing"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "spacing"}, "extent": [9389, 9398], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Shape Adjustment"], "extent": [10937, 10962], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [12309, 12413], "text": ["Available when ", {"text": ["Spine shape"], "type": "ui"}, " is \"Curve from second input\" and the node\u2019s second input is connected."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [12464, 12511], "text": ["Reverse the direction of the spine curve."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Reverse Direction"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "reversespinedirection"}, "extent": [12413, 12432], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [12551, 12620], "text": ["Rotate the spine curve around the line through its end points. "]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Axial Rotation"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "axialrotation"}, "extent": [12511, 12527], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [12655, 12762], "text": ["How much to blend the direction at the end of the curve with the orientation of the extrusion front. "]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Front Blend"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "srcdirblend"}, "extent": [12620, 12633], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [12796, 12909], "text": ["How much to blend the direction at the start of the curve with the orientation of the original edges/faces."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Back Blend"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "dstdirblend"}, "extent": [12762, 12774], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["External Spine"], "extent": [12269, 12309], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "external_spine"}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [12927, 13045], "text": ["These parameters let you scale the width of the bridge along its length, creating pinches and/bulges in the bridge."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [16003, 16084], "text": ["Scales the values of the ", {"text": ["Thickness ramp"], "type": "ui"}, " and/or ", {"text": ["Thickness attribute"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Thickness Scale"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "thicknessscale"}, "extent": [15957, 15974], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [16135, 16374], "text": ["If ", {"text": ["Spine Shape"], "type": "ui"}, " is \"Curve From Second Input\" (on the ", {"text": ["Spine"], "type": "ui"}, " tab), use this attribute on the external curve to control the thickness of the bridge. This is multiplied by the ", {"text": ["Thickness scale"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["added to"], "type": "em"}, " the thickness ramp."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Thickness Attribute"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "thicknessattrib"}, "extent": [16084, 16105], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [16418, 16652], "text": ["Controls the thickness of the bridge along its length. The horizontal axis represents the length of the bridge. Values of ", {"text": ["0.5"], "type": "code"}, " do no scaling. Values less than ", {"text": ["0.5"], "type": "code"}, " narrow the bridge. Values greater than ", {"text": ["0.5"], "type": "code"}, " widen the bridge."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Thickness Ramp"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "thicknessramp"}, "extent": [16374, 16390], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Thickness"], "extent": [12909, 12927], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [16864, 16937], "text": ["Scales the values of the ", {"text": ["Twist ramp"], "type": "ui"}, " and/or ", {"text": ["Twist attribute"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Twist Scale"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "twistscale"}, "extent": [16826, 16839], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [16980, 17196], "text": ["If ", {"text": ["Spine Shape"], "type": "ui"}, " is \"External\" (on the ", {"text": ["Spine"], "type": "ui"}, " tab), use this attribute on the external curve to control the twist of the bridge. This is multiplied by the ", {"text": ["Twist scale"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["added to"], "type": "em"}, " the twist ramp."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Twist Attribute"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "twistattrib"}, "extent": [16937, 16954], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "extent": [17238, 17494], "text": ["Controls the twist of the bridge along its length. The horizontal axis represents the length of the bridge. Values of ", {"text": ["0.5"], "type": "code"}, " represent no twist. Values less than ", {"text": ["0.5"], "type": "code"}, " twist in one direction, values greater than ", {"text": ["0.5"], "type": "code"}, " twist in the other direction."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Local Twist Ramp"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "twistramp"}, "extent": [17196, 17214], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Twist"], "extent": [13160, 13174], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Spine Control"], "extent": [10820, 10840], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [13373, 13442], "text": ["Multiply the extrusion distance by the value of this attribute."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Distance scale"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "localzscaleattrib"}, "extent": [13324, 13341], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [13455, 13518], "text": ["Multiply the inset amount by the value of this attribute."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Inset scale"], "role": "item", "extent": [13442, 13455], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [13567, 13630], "text": ["Multiply the twist amount by the value of this attribute."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Twist scale"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "localtwistscaleattrib"}, "extent": [13518, 13531], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [13681, 13751], "text": ["Multiply the number of divisions by the value of this attribute."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Divisions scale"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "localdivscaleattrib"}, "extent": [13630, 13647], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Local Attributes"], "extent": [13298, 13324], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [13772, 13891], "text": ["You can use these attributes to control the local transform space and extrusion amount of each individual component."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [13891, 14161], "text": ["If you're extruding faces, these should be primitive attributes, and the values are averaged from all faces in an extrusion front. If you're extruding edges, they should be point attributes, and the value of each edge is the average of the values on its two endpoints."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [14201, 14428], "text": ["Use this vector attribute as an edge/face\u2019s local X axis. The node makes this orthogonal to the local Z axis if it\u2019s not already. If the vector is ", {"text": ["0,0,0"], "type": "code"}, " the node ignores it. The node automatically normalizes the vector."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["X Direction"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "localxattrib"}, "extent": [14161, 14174], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [14464, 14655], "text": ["Use this vector attribute as an edge/face\u2019s local Z axis. This overrides the computed normal. If the vector is ", {"text": ["0,0,0"], "type": "code"}, " the node ignores it. The node automatically normalizes the vector."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Z Direction"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "localzattrib"}, "extent": [14428, 14441], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [14692, 14788], "text": ["Use this vector attribute as the edge/face\u2019s center. This overrides the computed centroid."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Center"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "localctrattrib"}, "extent": [14655, 14663], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [14808, 14872], "text": ["Scale the extrusion amount by the value of this attribute."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Z Scale"], "role": "item", "extent": [14788, 14808], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 3, "text": ["Local Frames"], "extent": [13751, 13772], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Local Control"], "extent": [13278, 13298], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [3842, 3854], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "related_item", "extent": [14881, 14907], "text": [" ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/polybridge", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/polybridge"}]}, {"indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "related_item", "extent": [14907, 14931], "text": [" ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/polybevel", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/polybevel"}]}, {"indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "related_item", "extent": [14931, 14954], "text": [" ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/extrude", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/extrude"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "related_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [14872, 14881], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["Poly Extrude"], "summary": ["Extrudes polygonal faces and edges."], "attrs": {"version": "2.0", "tags": "reshape, polygons, edges, model, boxup, core", "namespace": null, "internal": "polyextrude", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/polyextrude"}, "included": ["/nodes/sop/polybridge"], "type": "root"}